==English==
===Etymology===
{{Ger.}} Wendy: a proper name meaning "fair one" or "fair-haired"; shortened form of [[Gwendolyn]]. It is most famously used in J.M. Barrie's Book, '''Peter Pan'''.

===Pronunciation===
*jĕsʹĭkə, /ˈdʒɛsɪkə/, /<tt>"dZEsIk@</tt>/

===Proper noun===
'''Wendy'''
# A female [[given name]].

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[Wendi]]
*German: [[Wenda]]


